I already bought the roses.

1675
02:23:10,666 --> 02:23:11,958
Let's go.

1676
02:23:12,458 --> 02:23:13,458
Come on.

1677
02:23:14,333 --> 02:23:17,791
If there was no pain to endure,

1678
02:23:18,791 --> 02:23:21,458
why would anyone want to run a marathon?

1679
02:23:33,333 --> 02:23:35,458
They both ran for six hours,

1680
02:23:35,666 --> 02:23:37,916
slower than the fastest runner

1681
02:23:38,000 --> 02:23:40,166
by three and a half hours.

1682
02:23:41,250 --> 02:23:43,666
The finish line is there for all runners,

1683
02:23:44,000 --> 02:23:45,666
whether you're the first

1684
02:23:46,083 --> 02:23:48,333
or the 1,500th runner.

1685
02:23:48,750 --> 02:23:50,708
Everyone who crosses the finish line

1686
02:23:50,875 --> 02:23:54,333
will be treated as a winner.

1687
02:23:54,583 --> 02:23:55,666
By the way,

1688
02:23:56,333 --> 02:23:58,791
what did you say
to the devil at the 35-km mark?

1689
02:24:05,625 --> 02:24:07,083
She knew now that

1690
02:24:07,583 --> 02:24:10,083
despite what she told the devil,

1691
02:24:10,500 --> 02:24:13,083
she was not the same person anymore.

1692
02:24:14,416 --> 02:24:15,625
And this

1693
02:24:15,708 --> 02:24:19,916
is the only purpose humans live for.

1694
02:24:20,375 --> 02:24:22,041
Move forward

1695
02:24:22,125 --> 02:24:24,458
to cover the seven feet in front of you,

1696
02:24:24,833 --> 02:24:27,083
and look forward to the changes coming

1697
